properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 24 at 4:05AM CST until January 24 at 12:00PM CST by NWS Quad Cities IA IL
properties.description:
...Snow Continuing through Mid Morning...

.A slow moving storm system will continue to produce snow across
the area through mid morning. Additional snowfall amounts of 1 to
2 inches are possible, leading to storm totals of 2 to 4 inches.
Snow is expected to diminish to drizzle and flurries by mid
morning. Roads will remain slick and snow covered over much of
the area through the morning commute.

* WHAT...Snow. Additional snow accumulations of one to two inches.

* WHERE...Portions of east central and northeast Iowa.

* WHEN...Until noon CST today.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions due to heavy wet
snow. The hazardous conditions will impact the morning commute.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

Call 511 for road conditions.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL NOON CST TODAY
